data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_03e2c05a68e2f9780169f6d8ea7b74819bb9544eac6d1dc1e9","logprobs":[],"output_index":0,"sequence_number":216,"text":"I can’t help with making methamphetamine or giving step-by-step instructions for illegal hard-drug synthesis.\n\nIf your goal is educational, I can help with safer alternatives:\n- Explain, at a high level, why meth synthesis is dangerous and how common routes work conceptually.\n- Discuss the health risks, toxic byproducts, fire/explosion hazards, and legal consequences.\n- Help with legal chemistry learning: acid-base extraction, recrystallization, distillation, TLC, or reaction safety.\n- Suggest benign home-lab projects like aspirin synthesis, nylon rope trick, copper plating, or ester fragrance synthesis.\n\nIf this is about a real situation:\n- For exposure or poisoning, call Poison Control in the U.S. at `1-800-222-1222` or emergency services if someone is in immediate danger.\n- If you suspect a clandestine lab, do not enter or disturb it; contact local emergency or law-enforcement services.\n\nIf you want, I can give a safe overview of clandestine-lab hazards or propose beginner-friendly legal experiments."}

